wiki.summary: “Symphony” is a song by British dance trio Clean Bandit. It is the third single from their sophomore album after the success of “Tears” and their global hit “Rockabye” which topped the UK charts. The song went on to top the UK Charts as well in April becoming Clean bandit’s third and Zara Larsson’s first #1 single in the UK. “Symphony” features vocals from Zara Larsson with whom the band are touring with in 2017. This is the first collaboration between the artists. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “Symphony” is a song by British dance trio Clean Bandit. It is the third single from their sophomore album after the success of “Tears” and their global hit “Rockabye” which topped the UK charts. The song went on to top the UK Charts as well in April becoming Clean bandit’s third and Zara Larsson’s first #1 single in the UK. “Symphony” features vocals from Zara Larsson with whom the band are touring with in 2017. This is the first collaboration between the artists. They were filming the music video for the song in London on the last week of February. The track is also featured as the final track on Zara Larsson’s debut international album “So Good”. Read more on Last.fm.
